InterfaceBitmask.name: InterfaceBitmask
InterfaceBitmask.description: An Interface Bitmask used to enable or disable access or functionality of an interface in the system. Each bit in this object represents a network interface in the system consistent with the ifIndex object in MIB-II. The value for this object is interpreted as a bitfield, where the value of 1 means enabled. Examples of Usage: 1. For a system with the following interfaces : - Ethernet If = 1 - Loopback If = 2 - Wireless If 0 VAP 0 = 3 - Wireless If 0 VAP 1 = 4 - Wireless If 0 VAP 2 = 5 - Wireless If 0 VAP 3 = 6 - Wireless If 1 VAP 0 = 7 - Wireless If 1 VAP 1 = 8 - Wireless If 1 VAP 2 = 9 - Wireless If 1 VAP 3 = 10 Interface Bitmask usage: - 00000000 (0x00): All Interfaces disabled - 00000001 (0x01): Ethernet If enabled - 00000010 (0x02): Wireless If 0 VAP 0 enabled - 00000100 (0x03): Wireless If 0 VAP 1 enabled - 00001000 (0x04): Wireless If 0 VAP 2 enabled - 00010000 (0x06): Wireless If 0 VAP 3 enabled TBD: This has to be re-considered Note: The software loopback interface bit is ignored in the usage of the interface bitmask object.

wirelessIfPropertiesTable.name: wirelessIfPropertiesTable
wirelessIfPropertiesTable.description: This table contains information on the properties and capabilities of the wireless interface(s) present in the device.

wirelessIfPropertiesTableEntry.name: wirelessIfPropertiesTableEntry
wirelessIfPropertiesTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry in the wireless interface properties table.

wirelessIfPropertiesTableIndex.name: wirelessIfPropertiesTableIndex
wirelessIfPropertiesTableIndex.description: This parameter represents a unique value for each Wireless interface in the system and is used as index to this table.

wirelessIfPropertiesRadioStatus.name: wirelessIfPropertiesRadioStatus
wirelessIfPropertiesRadioStatus.description: This parameter is used to provide the status of the Wireless Radio interface. Select (1) to enable the wireless interface and (2) to disable the wireless interface.

wirelessIfOperationalMode.name: wirelessIfOperationalMode
wirelessIfOperationalMode.description: This parameter is used to set the wireless NIC Operational mode. Depending on the wireless NIC in the device different wireless operational modes can be configured. The object wirelessIfSupportedOperationalMode shows the supported modes and the possible supported modes for AP products: dot11b(1), dot11g(2), dot11ng(3), dot11a(4), dot11na(5)

wirelessIfSupportedOperationalMode.name: wirelessIfSupportedOperationalMode
wirelessIfSupportedOperationalMode.description: This parameter is used to set the wireless supported Operational mode.

wirelessIfCurrentChannelBandwidth.name: wirelessIfCurrentChannelBandwidth
wirelessIfCurrentChannelBandwidth.description: This parameter represents the current bandwidth that Wireless is currently operating on. It is represented in MHz

wirelessIfSupportedChannelBandwidth.name: wirelessIfSupportedChannelBandwidth
wirelessIfSupportedChannelBandwidth.description: This parameter represents the channel bandwidths that a wireless can support.

wirelessIfAutoChannelSelection.name: wirelessIfAutoChannelSelection
wirelessIfAutoChannelSelection.description: This parameter is used to configure the auto channel selection for wireless interface. Select (1) to enable the auto channel selection and (2) to disable the auto channel selection.

wirelessIfCurrentOperatingChannel.name: wirelessIfCurrentOperatingChannel
wirelessIfCurrentOperatingChannel.description: This parameter represents the user configured channel that the radio is configured to operate in. Note: It is possible that the currently active channel is different. To find the current active/operational channel refer to wirelessIfCurrentActiveChannel.

wirelessIfSupportedChannels.name: wirelessIfSupportedChannels
wirelessIfSupportedChannels.description: This parameter represents the channels that wireless can support.

wirelessIfAutoRateSelection.name: wirelessIfAutoRateSelection
wirelessIfAutoRateSelection.description: This parameter is used to configure the value for Auto Rate Selection for the wireless interface. Select (1) to enable the Auto Rate selection and (2) to disable the Auto Rate selection.

wirelessIfTransmittedRate.name: wirelessIfTransmittedRate
wirelessIfTransmittedRate.description: This parameter represents the number of rates transmitted for wireless.

wirelessIfSupportedRate.name: wirelessIfSupportedRate
wirelessIfSupportedRate.description: This parameter represents the number of rates supported for wireless.

wirelessIfVAPRTSThreshold.name: wirelessIfVAPRTSThreshold
wirelessIfVAPRTSThreshold.description: This parameter represents the maximum threshold for VAP RTS (Request To Send). The maximum threshold can be configured up to 2346.

wirelessIfVAPBeaconInterval.name: wirelessIfVAPBeaconInterval
wirelessIfVAPBeaconInterval.description: This parameter represents the time interval that a beacon takes for getting transmitted for wireless VAP. By default, the value is set to 100 ms.

wirelessIfTPC.name: wirelessIfTPC
wirelessIfTPC.description: This parameter represents the cell size that the transmitted power controls. It is measured in dBm. Please check the wirelessIfActiveTPC for current active TPC.

wirelessIfCellSize.name: wirelessIfCellSize
wirelessIfCellSize.description: This parameter represents the cell size of the wireless. By default, the cell size is configured to large. Select (1) for Small cell size, (2) for Medium cell size and (3) for Large cell size.

wirelessIfDTIM.name: wirelessIfDTIM
wirelessIfDTIM.description: This parameter represents the delivery traffic indication map period. This is the interval between the transmission of multicast frames on the wireless inteface. It is expressed in the Beacon messages. The recommended default value for this parameter is 1.

wirelessIfAntennaGain.name: wirelessIfAntennaGain
wirelessIfAntennaGain.description: This parameter is used to configure the antenna gain.

wirelessIfCurrentActiveChannel.name: wirelessIfCurrentActiveChannel
wirelessIfCurrentActiveChannel.description: This parameter represents the current active channel that wireless radio is operating on. It may be different from the configured channel represented by wirelessIfCurrentOperatingChannel.

wirelessIfSatelliteDensity.name: wirelessIfSatelliteDensity
wirelessIfSatelliteDensity.description: This parameter represents the density of the satellites for the BSU. It configures the BSU to accomodate the satellites for the specified range.

wirelessIfMPOperationalMode.name: wirelessIfMPOperationalMode
wirelessIfMPOperationalMode.description: This parameter is used to set the wireless NIC Operational mode for Tsunami Multi Point Products.

wirelessIfChannelWaitTime.name: wirelessIfChannelWaitTime
wirelessIfChannelWaitTime.description: This parameter is used to configure the DFS channel wait time.

wirelessIfActiveTPC.name: wirelessIfActiveTPC
wirelessIfActiveTPC.description: This parameter shows the active cell size that the transmitted power controls. It is measured in dBm

wirelessIfDfsNumSatWithRadarForFreqSwitc.name: wirelessIfDfsNumSatWithRadarForFreqSwitch
wirelessIfDfsNumSatWithRadarForFreqSwitc.description: This parameter represents the minimum number of satellites reporting RADAR for BSU to switch to a new best channel/frequency. The default value is (0) that indicates BSU to never switch to a new best channel/frequency for any number of satellites reporting RADAR.

wirelessIfDfsStatus.name: wirelessIfDfsStatus
wirelessIfDfsStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the DFS for SU. Configuring this parameter for BSU will not affecte BSU Status. 1 to enable the DFS, 2 to disable the DFS.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesTable.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesTable
wirelessIf11nPropertiesTable.description: This table holds the wireless11n configurations.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableEntry.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableEntry
wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for wireless11n properties table.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableIndex.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableIndex
wirelessIf11nPropertiesTableIndex.description: This parameter represents index to the wireless interface 11n table and this represents the wireless radios.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUStatus.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUStatus
wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUStatus.description: This parameter is used define the AMPDU status for wireless 11n interface. Select 1 to enable and 2 to disable the AMPDU status.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxNumFrames.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxNumFrames
wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxNumFrames.description: This parameter represents the Agregated MAC Protocol Data Unit (AMPDU) frames that are transmitted. It can be configured up to 64 frames.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxFrameSize.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxFrameSize
wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMPDUMaxFrameSize.description: This parameter is used to configure the maximum AMPDU frame size (in bytes) that can be transmitted.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUStatus.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUStatus
wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUStatus.description: This parameter is used define the AMSDU status for wireless 11n interface. Select 1 to enable and 2 to disable the AMSDU status.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUMaxFrameSize.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUMaxFrameSize
wirelessIf11nPropertiesAMSDUMaxFrameSize.description: This parameter shows the maximum AMSDU frame size (in bytes) that can be transmitted.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesFrequencyExtensio.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesFrequencyExtension
wirelessIf11nPropertiesFrequencyExtensio.description: This parameter is used to configure the frequency extension for the wireless interface. Select 1 to configure the UpperExtensionChannel and 2 to configure the LowerExtensionChannel.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesGuardInterval.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesGuardInterval
wirelessIf11nPropertiesGuardInterval.description: This parameter is used to configure the guard interval for the wireless interface. Select 1 for short guard interval as 400 nano seconds and 2 for full guard interval as 800 nano seconds.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesTxAntennas.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesTxAntennas
wirelessIf11nPropertiesTxAntennas.description: This parameter enables the transmission antennas. This is configured as bit-mask. Eg: 3 - 011 (binary value) - first and second antennas are enabled. 7 - 111 (binary value) - all three are enabled.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesRxAntennas.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesRxAntennas
wirelessIf11nPropertiesRxAntennas.description: This parameter enables the receiving antennas. This is configured as bit-mask. Eg: 3 - 011 (binary value) - first and second antennas are enabled. 7 - 111 (binary value) - all three are enabled.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesNumOfSpatialStrea.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesNumOfSpatialStreams
wirelessIf11nPropertiesNumOfSpatialStrea.description: This parameter is used to select the number of spatial streams for 11n.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedTxAntenn.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedTxAntennas
wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedTxAntenn.description: This parameter shows the number of supported Tx antennas.

wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedRxAntenn.name: wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedRxAntennas
wirelessIf11nPropertiesSupportedRxAntenn.description: This parameter shows the number of supported Rx antennas.

wirelessIfVAPTable.name: wirelessIfVAPTable
wirelessIfVAPTable.description: This table holds the wireless VAP (virtual access point) configurations.

wirelessIfVAPTableEntry.name: wirelessIfVAPTableEntry
wirelessIfVAPTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the wireless VAP table.

wirelessIfVAPTableIndex.name: wirelessIfVAPTableIndex
wirelessIfVAPTableIndex.description: This parameter is used to configure the wireless VAP table. Select 1 represents Wifi0 (radio-0) and 2 represents Wifi1 (radio-1).

wirelessIfVAPTableSecIndex.name: wirelessIfVAPTableSecIndex
wirelessIfVAPTableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents the VAPs and used as secondary index to this table.

wirelessIfVAPType.name: wirelessIfVAPType
wirelessIfVAPType.description: This parameter is used to configure the type of VAP. Select 1 for AP.

wirelessIfVAPSSID.name: wirelessIfVAPSSID
wirelessIfVAPSSID.description: This parameter is used to represent the wireless card SSID name (wireless network name).

wirelessIfVAPBSSID.name: wirelessIfVAPBSSID
wirelessIfVAPBSSID.description: This parameter represents the MAC address for the VAP BSSID.

wirelessIfVAPBroadcastSSID.name: wirelessIfVAPBroadcastSSID
wirelessIfVAPBroadcastSSID.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the broadcast wireless VAP SSID. A single entry in the SSID table can be enabled to broadcast SSID in beacon messages. Select 1 to enable, 2 to disable

wirelessIfVAPFragmentationThreshold.name: wirelessIfVAPFragmentationThreshold
wirelessIfVAPFragmentationThreshold.description: This parameter is used to configure the fragmentation threshold for the wireless VAP. By default, the value is set to 2346.

wirelessIfVAPSecurityProfileName.name: wirelessIfVAPSecurityProfileName
wirelessIfVAPSecurityProfileName.description: This parameter allows you to configure the Security profile name for Wireless VAP.

wirelessIfVAPRadiusProfileName.name: wirelessIfVAPRadiusProfileName
wirelessIfVAPRadiusProfileName.description: This parameter allows you to configure the RADIUS profile name for Wireless VAP.

wirelessIfVAPVLANID.name: wirelessIfVAPVLANID
wirelessIfVAPVLANID.description: This parameter is used to represent the VLAN ID for the wireless VAP. Select any value between 1 - 4094 to tag the VLAN ids and -1 to untag the VLAN ids.

wirelessIfVAPVLANPriority.name: wirelessIfVAPVLANPriority
wirelessIfVAPVLANPriority.description: This parameter is used to configure the VLAN priority for Wireless VAP. By default the value is set to 0.

wirelessIfVAPQoSProfileName.name: wirelessIfVAPQoSProfileName
wirelessIfVAPQoSProfileName.description: This parameter is used to configure the profile name for the Wireless VAP QoS.

wirelessIfVAPMACACLStatus.name: wirelessIfVAPMACACLStatus
wirelessIfVAPMACACLStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the MAC access control list.

wirelessIfVAPRadiusMACACLStatus.name: wirelessIfVAPRadiusMACACLStatus
wirelessIfVAPRadiusMACACLStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the MAC ACL for Radius Profiles

wirelessIfVAPRadiusAccStatus.name: wirelessIfVAPRadiusAccStatus
wirelessIfVAPRadiusAccStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the Radius Accounting Stats capture.

wirelessIfVAPStatus.name: wirelessIfVAPStatus
wirelessIfVAPStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the VAP. Select 1 to enable the VAP, 2 to disable the VAP and 3 to delete the VAP.

wirelessIfWORPTable.name: wirelessIfWORPTable
wirelessIfWORPTable.description: This table holds the wireless WORP protocol configurations

wirelessIfWORPTableEntry.name: wirelessIfWORPTableEntry
wirelessIfWORPTableEntry.description: This object represents the entry for the wireless WORP table

wirelessIfWORPTableIndex.name: wirelessIfWORPTableIndex
wirelessIfWORPTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the radio for which the WORP is enabled and index to the wirelessIfWORPTable.

wirelessIfWORPMode.name: wirelessIfWORPMode
wirelessIfWORPMode.description: This parameter displays the worp mode of operation.

wirelessIfWORPBaseStationName.name: wirelessIfWORPBaseStationName
wirelessIfWORPBaseStationName.description: This parameter represents the name of the BSU for which it can register. This configuration is valid only on SU. If this field is empty then SU is allowed to register with any BSU.

wirelessIfWORPNetworkName.name: wirelessIfWORPNetworkName
wirelessIfWORPNetworkName.description: This parameter represents the name of the Network of the WORP Interface.

wirelessIfWORPMaxSatellites.name: wirelessIfWORPMaxSatellites
wirelessIfWORPMaxSatellites.description: This parameter represents the maximum number of SUs allowed to register on this BSU. This configuration is valid only on BSU.

wirelessIfWORPMTU.name: wirelessIfWORPMTU
wirelessIfWORPMTU.description: This parameter represents to maximum size of a frame sent from the WORP interface.

wirelessIfWORPSuperPacketing.name: wirelessIfWORPSuperPacketing
wirelessIfWORPSuperPacketing.description: This parameter represents the status of bundling multiple ethernet frames in one single WORP Jumbo frame

wirelessIfWORPSleepMode.name: wirelessIfWORPSleepMode
wirelessIfWORPSleepMode.description: This parameter represents the status of sleep mode. This Configuration is valid only on BSU. If there is no data available to transfer b/w BSU & SU, BSU will keep the SU state in sleep state and polls that particular SU for every 4 seconds to just to maintain the WORP link.

wirelessIfWORPMultiFrameBursting.name: wirelessIfWORPMultiFrameBursting
wirelessIfWORPMultiFrameBursting.description: This parameter enables WORP protocol to allow each side, BSU or SU, to send a burst of multiple data messages instead of a single data message.

wirelessIfWORPRegistrationTimeout.name: wirelessIfWORPRegistrationTimeout
wirelessIfWORPRegistrationTimeout.description: This parameter represents the registration procedure timeout period for WORP interface.

wirelessIfWORPRetries.name: wirelessIfWORPRetries
wirelessIfWORPRetries.description: This parameter represents the number of times the same worp frame need to be re-Transmitted, if it is not acknowledged by the peer.

wirelessIfWORPTxRate.name: wirelessIfWORPTxRate
wirelessIfWORPTxRate.description: This parameter represents the WORP interface transmission rate. Please check the object wirelessIfWORPSupportedTxRate for supported rates.

wirelessIfWORPSupportedTxRate.name: wirelessIfWORPSupportedTxRate
wirelessIfWORPSupportedTxRate.description: This parameter displays the supported transmission rate based on Channel Bandwdith, Guard Interval and Number of Spacial Streams configuration.

wirelessIfWORPInputBandwidthLimit.name: wirelessIfWORPInputBandwidthLimit
wirelessIfWORPInputBandwidthLimit.description: This parameters represents the Bandwidth limit on Input direction. Default limit & maximum limit are based on the license file.

wirelessIfWORPOutputBandwidthLimit.name: wirelessIfWORPOutputBandwidthLimit
wirelessIfWORPOutputBandwidthLimit.description: This parameter represents the Bandwidth limit on Output direction. Default limit & maximum limit are based on the license file.

wirelessIfWORPBandwidthLimitType.name: wirelessIfWORPBandwidthLimitType
wirelessIfWORPBandwidthLimitType.description: This parameter represents the bandwidth limit type - shaping or policing.

wirelessIfWORPSecurityProfileIndex.name: wirelessIfWORPSecurityProfileIndex
wirelessIfWORPSecurityProfileIndex.description: This parameter allows to configure the Security profile for the WORP interface based on the index of the profile name and this is Valid only on BSU.

wirelessIfWORPRadiusProfileIndex.name: wirelessIfWORPRadiusProfileIndex
wirelessIfWORPRadiusProfileIndex.description: This parameter allows to configure the Radius profile for the WORP interface based on the index of the profile name and this is Valid only on BSU..

wirelessIfWORPMACACLStatus.name: wirelessIfWORPMACACLStatus
wirelessIfWORPMACACLStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the MAC access control list. This configuration is Valid only on BSU.

wirelessIfWORPRadiusMACACLStatus.name: wirelessIfWORPRadiusMACACLStatus
wirelessIfWORPRadiusMACACLStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the MAC ACL for Radius Profiles. This configuration is Valid only on BSU.

wirelessIfWORPRadiusAccStatus.name: wirelessIfWORPRadiusAccStatus
wirelessIfWORPRadiusAccStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the Radius Accounting Stats capture. This configuration is Valid only on BSU and currently this is not accessible.

wirelessIfWORPIntfMacAddress.name: wirelessIfWORPIntfMacAddress
wirelessIfWORPIntfMacAddress.description: This parameter represents the MAC address of the wireless interface card.

wirelessIfWORPAutoMultiFrameBursting.name: wirelessIfWORPAutoMultiFrameBursting
wirelessIfWORPAutoMultiFrameBursting.description: This parameter enables WORP protocol to allow each side, BSU or SU, to send a burst of multiple data messages based on QOS priority instead of a single data message.

wirelessIfDDRSTable.name: wirelessIfDDRSTable
wirelessIfDDRSTable.description: This table holds the WORP DDRS (Dynamic Data Rate Selection) feature configurations.

wirelessIfDDRSTableEntry.name: wirelessIfDDRSTableEntry
wirelessIfDDRSTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for DDRS table.

wirelessIfDDRSTableIndex.name: wirelessIfDDRSTableIndex
wirelessIfDDRSTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the DDRS table and indirectly represent the wireless interface index.

wirelessIfDDRSStatus.name: wirelessIfDDRSStatus
wirelessIfDDRSStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable the DDRS feature for the interface.

wirelessIfDDRSDefDataRate.name: wirelessIfDDRSDefDataRate
wirelessIfDDRSDefDataRate.description: This default data rate shall be used as WORP default data rate only when the DDRS is enabled. The rates defined in wirelessIfWORPTxRate are used as default.

wirelessIfDDRSMaxDataRate.name: wirelessIfDDRSMaxDataRate
wirelessIfDDRSMaxDataRate.description: This parameter is used to limit the maximum possible data rate that is set by DDRS.

wirelessIfDDRSIncrAvgSNRThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSIncrAvgSNRThrld
wirelessIfDDRSIncrAvgSNRThrld.description: This parameter is used to specify the average SNR threshold for data rate increase. The value should be in dB and in the range of 0..50 dB.

wirelessIfDDRSIncrReqSNRThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSIncrReqSNRThrld
wirelessIfDDRSIncrReqSNRThrld.description: This parameter is to specify minimum required SNR threshold for data rate increase. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB.

wirelessIfDDRSDecrReqSNRThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSDecrReqSNRThrld
wirelessIfDDRSDecrReqSNRThrld.description: This parameter is to specify minimum required SNR threshold for data rate decrease. The value should be in dB and in the range 0..50 dB.

wirelessIfDDRSIncrReTxPercentThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSIncrReTxPercentThrld
wirelessIfDDRSIncrReTxPercentThrld.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for DDRS data rate increase.

wirelessIfDDRSDecrReTxPercentThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSDecrReTxPercentThrld
wirelessIfDDRSDecrReTxPercentThrld.description: This object specifies the threshold percentage of retransmissions for DDRS data rate decrease.

wirelessIfDDRSAggressiveIndex.name: wirelessIfDDRSAggressiveIndex
wirelessIfDDRSAggressiveIndex.description: This object specifies the aggressiveness of the ddrs algorithm.

wirelessIfDDRSChainBalThrld.name: wirelessIfDDRSChainBalThrld
wirelessIfDDRSChainBalThrld.description: This object specifies the Mimo Chain Balance threshold.

wirelessIfDDRSRateBackOffInt.name: wirelessIfDDRSRateBackOffInt
wirelessIfDDRSRateBackOffInt.description: This object specifies the Rate Backoff Interval.

wirelessIfDDRSRateBlackListInt.name: wirelessIfDDRSRateBlackListInt
wirelessIfDDRSRateBlackListInt.description: This object specifies the Rate Blacklist Interval.

ethernetIfPropertiesTable.name: ethernetIfPropertiesTable
ethernetIfPropertiesTable.description: This table shows the ethernet interface(s) properties for the device.

ethernetIfPropertiesTableEntry.name: ethernetIfPropertiesTableEntry
ethernetIfPropertiesTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the Ethernet Interface Properties table.

ethernetIfPropertiesTableIndex.name: ethernetIfPropertiesTableIndex
ethernetIfPropertiesTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the physical interface and used as index to this table.

ethernetIfMACAddress.name: ethernetIfMACAddress
ethernetIfMACAddress.description: This parameter represents the MAC address for the ethernet interface.

ethernetIfSupportedSpeed.name: ethernetIfSupportedSpeed
ethernetIfSupportedSpeed.description: This parameter shows the supported speeds for the ethernet interface.

ethernetIfSupportedTxMode.name: ethernetIfSupportedTxMode
ethernetIfSupportedTxMode.description: This parameter shows the supported transmit modes of the ethernet interface.

ethernetIfTxModeAndSpeed.name: ethernetIfTxModeAndSpeed
ethernetIfTxModeAndSpeed.description: This parameter is used to configure the Transmit Mode and speed of the ethernet interface.

ethernetIfSupportedModes.name: ethernetIfSupportedModes
ethernetIfSupportedModes.description: This parameter is used to display the supported modes on ethernet interface.

ethernetIfAdminStatus.name: ethernetIfAdminStatus
ethernetIfAdminStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the admin status for the ethernet interface.

ethernetIfAutoShutDown.name: ethernetIfAutoShutDown
ethernetIfAutoShutDown.description: This parameter is used to configure AutoShutDown for the ethernet interface. i.e. Ethernet interface will be automatically UP/DOWN depending upon the wireless link

wirelessSecurityCfgTable.name: wirelessSecurityCfgTable
wirelessSecurityCfgTable.description: This table is used to specify the security configuration for the wireless interface(s) in the access point.

wirelessSecurityCfgTableEntry.name: wirelessSecurityCfgTableEntry
wirelessSecurityCfgTableEntry.description: This parameter represents an entry in the wireless security configuration table. This table supports up to 8 entries.

wirelessSecurityCfgTableIndex.name: wirelessSecurityCfgTableIndex
wirelessSecurityCfgTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as index to the wireless security configuration table.

wirelessSecurityCfgprofileName.name: wirelessSecurityCfgprofileName
wirelessSecurityCfgprofileName.description: This paramater represents user defined profile name for security configuration.

wirelessSecurityCfgAuthenticationMode.name: wirelessSecurityCfgAuthenticationMode
wirelessSecurityCfgAuthenticationMode.description: This parameter is used to configure the security authentication mode for wireless. Select (1) - None (no security), (2) - WEP (Wired Equivalent Privacy), (3) - PSK (Pre-shared key), (4) - dotlx (802.1x authentication) and (5) - worp (Wireless Outdoor Router Protocol).

wirelessSecurityCfgKeyIndex.name: wirelessSecurityCfgKeyIndex
wirelessSecurityCfgKeyIndex.description: This parameter represents the encryption key index that is used to encrypt data that is sent via wireless interface(s).

wirelessSecurityCfgKey1.name: wirelessSecurityCfgKey1
wirelessSecurityCfgKey1.description: This parameter represents the key 1 used for wireless security configuration. The key lengths 5/13/16 in ASCII or 10/26/32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the WEP(64/128/152-bit) encryption respectively. The key lengths 16 in ASCII or 32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the TKIP(128-bit) or AES-CCM(128-bit) encryption.

wirelessSecurityCfgdot1xWepKeyLength.name: wirelessSecurityCfgdot1xWepKeyLength
wirelessSecurityCfgdot1xWepKeyLength.description: This parameter is used configure the length of the security key. Select WEP64 if you want to have a security key for 64 characters or WEP128 for security key length of 128 characters.

wirelessSecurityCfgEncryptionType.name: wirelessSecurityCfgEncryptionType
wirelessSecurityCfgEncryptionType.description: This parameter is used to configure the encryption key type for wireless security. Select 0 for no security 1 for WEP, 2 for WPA (TKIP), 3 for WPA2(AES), 4 for WPA/WPA2 (AES-TKIP) 5 for WPA2 (AES-CCM). 6 for TKIP -- Used only for TMP/QB products 7 for AES-CCM -- Used only for TMP/QB products.

wirelessSecurityCfgPSK.name: wirelessSecurityCfgPSK
wirelessSecurityCfgPSK.description: This parameter is used to configure the pre-share key. The default key is 123456789. This parameter is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return astericks

wirelessSecurityCfgRekeyingInterval.name: wirelessSecurityCfgRekeyingInterval
wirelessSecurityCfgRekeyingInterval.description: This parameter represents the key re-negotiation time in case of dynamic WEP, WPA/WPA-2 (personal/enterprise) security mechanisms.

wirelessSecurityCfgEntryStatus.name: wirelessSecurityCfgEntryStatus
wirelessSecurityCfgEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the entry status of wireless security configuration table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

wirelessSecurityCfgNetworkSecret.name: wirelessSecurityCfgNetworkSecret
wirelessSecurityCfgNetworkSecret.description: This parameter represents a secret password of an SU that tallies with the BSU's password for authentic registration.

wirelessSecurityCfgKey2.name: wirelessSecurityCfgKey2
wirelessSecurityCfgKey2.description: This parameter represents the key 2 used for wireless security configuration. The key lengths 5/13/16 in ASCII or 10/26/32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the WEP(64/128/152-bit) encryption respectively. The key lengths 16 in ASCII or 32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the TKIP(128-bit) or AES-CCM(128-bit) encryption.

wirelessSecurityCfgKey3.name: wirelessSecurityCfgKey3
wirelessSecurityCfgKey3.description: This parameter represents the key 3 used for wireless security configuration. The key lengths 5/13/16 in ASCII or 10/26/32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the WEP(64/128/152-bit) encryption respectively. The key lengths 16 in ASCII or 32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the TKIP(128-bit) or AES-CCM(128-bit) encryption.

wirelessSecurityCfgKey4.name: wirelessSecurityCfgKey4
wirelessSecurityCfgKey4.description: This parameter represents the key 4 used for wireless security configuration. The key lengths 5/13/16 in ASCII or 10/26/32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the WEP(64/128/152-bit) encryption respectively. The key lengths 16 in ASCII or 32 in HEXADECIMAL configures the TKIP(128-bit) or AES-CCM(128-bit) encryption.

radiusSrvProfileTable.name: radiusSrvProfileTable
radiusSrvProfileTable.description: This table contains the radius server configuration profiles.

radiusSrvProfileTableEntry.name: radiusSrvProfileTableEntry
radiusSrvProfileTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the radius server profile table.

radiusSrvProfileTableIndex.name: radiusSrvProfileTableIndex
radiusSrvProfileTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the user defined profiles for RADIUS Server.

radiusSrvProfileTableSecIndex.name: radiusSrvProfileTableSecIndex
radiusSrvProfileTableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents the user defined secondary profiles for RADIUS server. Maximum profiles are 4.

radiusSrvProfileType.name: radiusSrvProfileType
radiusSrvProfileType.description: This parameter represents the RADIUS Server profile type. Select (1) for Primary Authentication Server, (2) for Secondary Authentication Server, (3) for Primary Accounting Server, and (4) for Secondary Accounting Server.

radiusSrvIPADDR.name: radiusSrvIPADDR
radiusSrvIPADDR.description: This parameter is used to specify the RADIUS Server IP Address. Its default value is 169.254.128.133.

radiusSrvServerPort.name: radiusSrvServerPort
radiusSrvServerPort.description: This parameter represents the RADIUS server authentication port and the default value is 1812.

radiusSrvProfileServerSharedSecret.name: radiusSrvProfileServerSharedSecret
radiusSrvProfileServerSharedSecret.description: This parameter represents the shared secret between the RADIUS server and client. It is logically treated as write-only and should return the information in asterisks.

radiusSrvProfileTableEntryStatus.name: radiusSrvProfileTableEntryStatus
radiusSrvProfileTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the entry status of RADIUS server profile table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

radiusSupProfileTable.name: radiusSupProfileTable
radiusSupProfileTable.description: This table contains the radius support profile table configurations.

radiusSupProfileTableEntry.name: radiusSupProfileTableEntry
radiusSupProfileTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the radius support profile table.

radiusSupProfileTableIndex.name: radiusSupProfileTableIndex
radiusSupProfileTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the radius support profile table. Each index corresponds to the one profile name in the radius server profile table

radiusSupProfileName.name: radiusSupProfileName
radiusSupProfileName.description: This parameter represents the RADIUS profile name, only one profile is supported.

radiusSupProfileMaxReTransmissions.name: radiusSupProfileMaxReTransmissions
radiusSupProfileMaxReTransmissions.description: This parameter represents the number of times the radius request message to be sent to RADIUS server after the expiry of response time.

radiusSupProfileMsgResponseTime.name: radiusSupProfileMsgResponseTime
radiusSupProfileMsgResponseTime.description: This parameter represents the wait time in the RADIUS client for the response message from RADIUS server.

radiusSupProfileReAuthenticationPeriod.name: radiusSupProfileReAuthenticationPeriod
radiusSupProfileReAuthenticationPeriod.description: The parameter represents the time interval within which the reauthentication of the 802.1x enabled station happens.

radiusSupProfileTableEntryStatus.name: radiusSupProfileTableEntryStatus
radiusSupProfileTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the entry status of RADIUS supported profile table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2

macaclProfileTable.name: macaclProfileTable
macaclProfileTable.description: This table contains the MAC access control profile configurations.

macaclProfileTableEntry.name: macaclProfileTableEntry
macaclProfileTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the MAC access control profile table.

macaclProfileTableIndex.name: macaclProfileTableIndex
macaclProfileTableIndex.description: User defined profiles for MAC Access Control List. Max. number of profiles are 16.

macaclProfileName.name: macaclProfileName
macaclProfileName.description: This parameter represents the unique name MAC ACL profile.

macaclOperationType.name: macaclOperationType
macaclOperationType.description: This parameter is used o configure the type of MAC ACL profile. Select (1) to allow and (2) to deny.

macaclTableEntryStatus.name: macaclTableEntryStatus
macaclTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the security MAC ACL profile. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

macaclAddrTable.name: macaclAddrTable
macaclAddrTable.description: This table holds MAC access control list addresses.

macaclAddrTableEntry.name: macaclAddrTableEntry
macaclAddrTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the MAC access control list address table.

macaclAddrTableIndex.name: macaclAddrTableIndex
macaclAddrTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the user defined profiles for MAC ACL Address. Max. profiles are 16 profiles.

macaclAddrTableSecIndex.name: macaclAddrTableSecIndex
macaclAddrTableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents the user defined secondary profiles for MAC ACL Address. Maximum entries are 64 -- one entry per station

macaclAddrTableMACAddress.name: macaclAddrTableMACAddress
macaclAddrTableMACAddress.description: This parameter represents the valid MAC address for MAC ACL.

macaclAddrComment.name: macaclAddrComment
macaclAddrComment.description: This parameter displays a valid comment for MAC ACL Address.

macaclAddrTableEntryStatus.name: macaclAddrTableEntryStatus
macaclAddrTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the security MAC ACL Address. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

qosProfileTable.name: qosProfileTable
qosProfileTable.description: This table holds the various profiles for QOS (quality of service) configuration.

qosProfileTableEntry.name: qosProfileTableEntry
qosProfileTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the qos profile table.This table supports one entry.

qosProfileTableIndex.name: qosProfileTableIndex
qosProfileTableIndex.description: This parameter represents user defined profiles for Quality of Service (QoS).

qosProfileName.name: qosProfileName
qosProfileName.description: This parameter displays the name of the QoS profile that has been assigned.

qosProfileTablePolicyName.name: qosProfileTablePolicyName
qosProfileTablePolicyName.description: This parameter displays the QoS Policy profile name.

qosProfileEDCAProfileName.name: qosProfileEDCAProfileName
qosProfileEDCAProfileName.description: This parameter displays the name for QoS EDCA profile.

qosProfileTableQoSNACKStatus.name: qosProfileTableQoSNACKStatus
qosProfileTableQoSNACKStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the QoS profile ACK.

qoSPolicyTable.name: qoSPolicyTable
qoSPolicyTable.description: This table contains the QOS policy configurations.

qoSPolicyTableEntry.name: qoSPolicyTableEntry
qoSPolicyTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the qos policy table.

qoSPolicyTableIndex.name: qoSPolicyTableIndex
qoSPolicyTableIndex.description: This parameter represents user defined profiles for QoS Policy list.

qoSPolicyTableSecIndex.name: qoSPolicyTableSecIndex
qoSPolicyTableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents user defined secondary profiles. They are inbound layer2 -1, inbound layer3 -2, outbound layer2 -3 and outbound layer3 -4

qoSPolicyTablePolicyName.name: qoSPolicyTablePolicyName
qoSPolicyTablePolicyName.description: This parameter displays the QoS policy name.

qoSPolicyType.name: qoSPolicyType
qoSPolicyType.description: This parameter configures the QoS Policy type. They can be configured as the following: inbound layer2(1), inbound layer3(2), outbound layer2(3) and outbound layer3(4)

qoSPolicyPriorityMapping.name: qoSPolicyPriorityMapping
qoSPolicyPriorityMapping.description: This parameter is used as the primary index to the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table.

qoSPolicyMarkingStatus.name: qoSPolicyMarkingStatus
qoSPolicyMarkingStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable QoS Policy markings. Select (1) to enable, (2) to disable, and (3) for not supported option.

qoSPolicyTableEntryStatus.name: qoSPolicyTableEntryStatus
qoSPolicyTableEntryStatus.description: The parameter is used to configure the QoS Policy Table status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

wirelessQoSEDCATable.name: wirelessQoSEDCATable
wirelessQoSEDCATable.description: This table holds the wireless QOS EDCA (enhanced distributed channel access) configurations.

wirelessQoSEDCATableEntry.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableEntry
wirelessQoSEDCATableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the wireless QOS EDCA table.

wirelessQoSEDCATableIndex.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableIndex
wirelessQoSEDCATableIndex.description: This parameter is user defined profiles for Wireless QoS EDCA. Max profile that user can define is 1.

wirelessQoSEDCATableSecIndex.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableSecIndex
wirelessQoSEDCATableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents the user defined secondary profiles for Wireless QoS EDCA. Maximum profiles are 4. BK -1 (back ground), BE -2 (best effort), VI -3 (video), VO -4 (voice)

wirelessQoSEDCATableProfileName.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableProfileName
wirelessQoSEDCATableProfileName.description: This parameter displays the name for the Wireless QoS EDCA profile.

wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmin.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmin
wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmin.description: This parameter is used to configure the CW(Contention Window) min value for the wireless QoS EDCA profile. It can be configured up to 255 value. If this value is configured lower, then this increases the priority of the access category.

wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmax.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmax
wirelessQoSEDCATableCWmax.description: This parameter is used to configure the CW(Contention window) Max value for the wireless QoS EDCA profile. This value can be configured up to 65535. If this value id confiured to a lower value, then this increases the priority of access category.

wirelessQoSEDCATableAIFSN.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAIFSN
wirelessQoSEDCATableAIFSN.description: This parameter is used to configure the AIFSN (Arbitrary Inter Frame Space Number) value for the wireless QoS EDCA profile. It can be configured up to 15. If this value is configured lower,then this increases the priority of the access category.

wirelessQoSEDCATableTXOP.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableTXOP
wirelessQoSEDCATableTXOP.description: This parameter is used to configure TXOP(transmission oppurtunities) value for Wireless QoS EDCA. The values can be configured up to 65535. If this value for this parameter is configured lower, then this decreases the priority of the access category.

wirelessQoSEDCATableACM.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableACM
wirelessQoSEDCATableACM.description: This parameter is used to enable or disable the value for Addmission Control Mandatory. If ACM value is set to enable for a particular access category, then certain procedures needs to followed for using that access category.

wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmin.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmin
wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmin.description: This parameter is used to configure the minimum value for APCWmin. It can be configured upto 32767.

wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmax.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmax
wirelessQoSEDCATableAPCWmax.description: This parameter is used to configure the maximum value for APCWmax. It can be configured upto 32767.

wirelessQoSEDCATableAPAIFSN.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAPAIFSN
wirelessQoSEDCATableAPAIFSN.description: This parameter is used to configure the value fo APAIFSN(Arbitration Inter-Frame Space Number). The value for the APAIFSN can be configured up to 15

wirelessQoSEDCATableAPTXOP.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAPTXOP
wirelessQoSEDCATableAPTXOP.description: This parameter is used to configure the APTXOP (transmission oppurtunities) for the QoS EDCA profile. If the value is set to 0, then only one MPDU or MSDU can be transmitted

wirelessQoSEDCATableAPACM.name: wirelessQoSEDCATableAPACM
wirelessQoSEDCATableAPACM.description: This parameter is used to configure the APACM for the QoS EDCA profile. Select (1) to enable the profile and (2) to disable it.

l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable
l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTable.description: This table is used to configure Quality of Service mappings between 802.1D and 802.1p priorities.

l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry
l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableEntry.description: This parameter represents entries in the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p Mapping Table.

l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex
l2l3QoSDot1DToDot1pMappingTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as the primary index to the QoS 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table. This is based on the QoS profile.

l2l3QoSDot1dPriority.name: l2l3QoSDot1dPriority
l2l3QoSDot1dPriority.description: This parameter is used to specify the 802.1d priority and is used as the secondary index to the 802.1D to 802.1p mapping table.

l2l3QoSDot1pPriority.name: l2l3QoSDot1pPriority
l2l3QoSDot1pPriority.description: This parameter is used to specify the 802.1D priority to be mapped to a 802.1p priority

l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable
l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTable.description: This table is used to configure Quality of Service mappings between 802.1D to IP DSCP (Differentiated Services Code Point) priorities.

l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry
l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableEntry.description: This parameter represents entries in the 802.1D to IP DSCP Mapping Table.

l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex.name: l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex
l2l3QoSDot1DToIPDSCPMappingTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as the primary index to the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table.

l2l3QoSDot1dPriorityIPDSCP.name: l2l3QoSDot1dPriorityIPDSCP
l2l3QoSDot1dPriorityIPDSCP.description: This parameter is used to specify the 802.1D priority and is used as the secondary index to the 802.1D to IP DSCP mapping table.

l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityLowerLimit.name: l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityLowerLimit
l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityLowerLimit.description: This parameter is used to specify IP DSCP lower limit.

l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityUpperLimit.name: l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityUpperLimit
l2l3QoSDSCPPriorityUpperLimit.description: This parameter is used to specify IP DSCP upper limit.

worpQoSPIRMacTable.name: worpQoSPIRMacTable
worpQoSPIRMacTable.description: This Table holds the MAC Address details for Packet Identification Rule Clasification.

worpQoSPIRMacTableEntry.name: worpQoSPIRMacTableEntry
worpQoSPIRMacTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the worpQoSPIRMacTable.

worpQoSPIRMacTableIndex.name: worpQoSPIRMacTableIndex
worpQoSPIRMacTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the table.

worpQoSPIRMacAddr.name: worpQoSPIRMacAddr
worpQoSPIRMacAddr.description: This parameter specifies the MAC Address which can be used for PIR classification.

worpQoSPIRMacMask.name: worpQoSPIRMacMask
worpQoSPIRMacMask.description: This parameter specifies the MAC Address mask for the worpQoSPIRMacAddr.

worpQoSPIRMacComment.name: worpQoSPIRMacComment
worpQoSPIRMacComment.description: This parameter specifies the comment for the mac entry.

worpQoSPIRMacTableEntryStatus.name: worpQoSPIRMacTableEntryStatus
worpQoSPIRMacTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the worpQoSPIRMacTable status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

worpQoSPIRIPTable.name: worpQoSPIRIPTable
worpQoSPIRIPTable.description: This Table holds the IP Address details for PIR (Packet Identification Rule) Clasification.

worpQoSPIRIPTableEntry.name: worpQoSPIRIPTableEntry
worpQoSPIRIPTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the worpQoSPIRIPTable.

worpQoSPIRIPTableIndex.name: worpQoSPIRIPTableIndex
worpQoSPIRIPTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the table.

worpQoSPIRIPAddr.name: worpQoSPIRIPAddr
worpQoSPIRIPAddr.description: This parameter specifies the IP Address which can be used for PIR classification.

worpQoSPIRIPSubMask.name: worpQoSPIRIPSubMask
worpQoSPIRIPSubMask.description: This parameter specifies the Subnet Mask for the worpQoSPIRIPAddr.

worpQoSPIRIPComment.name: worpQoSPIRIPComment
worpQoSPIRIPComment.description: This parameter specifies the comment for the IP Address entry.

worpQoSPIRIPTableEntryStatus.name: worpQoSPIRIPTableEntryStatus
worpQoSPIRIPTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the worpQoSPIRIPTable status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

worpQoSPIRPortTable.name: worpQoSPIRPortTable
worpQoSPIRPortTable.description: This Table holds the TCP/UDP Port details for PIR (Packet Identification Rule) Clasification.

worpQoSPIRPortTableEntry.name: worpQoSPIRPortTableEntry
worpQoSPIRPortTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the worpQoSPIRPortTable.

worpQoSPIRPortTableIndex.name: worpQoSPIRPortTableIndex
worpQoSPIRPortTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the table.

worpQoSPIRStartPort.name: worpQoSPIRStartPort
worpQoSPIRStartPort.description: This parameter specifies the Starting TCP/UDP Port Number which can be used for PIR classification.

worpQoSPIREndPort.name: worpQoSPIREndPort
worpQoSPIREndPort.description: This parameter specifies the Ending TCP/UDP Port Number which can be used for PIR classification.

worpQoSPIRPortComment.name: worpQoSPIRPortComment
worpQoSPIRPortComment.description: This parameter specifies the comment for the TCP/UDP Port entry.

worpQoSPIRPortTableEntryStatus.name: worpQoSPIRPortTableEntryStatus
worpQoSPIRPortTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the worpQoSPIRPortTable status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6.

worpQoSPIRMapTable.name: worpQoSPIRMapTable
worpQoSPIRMapTable.description: This Table holds the Mapping information between PIR MAC Table entries, PIR IP Table entries, PIR Port Table entries with PIR Table.

worpQoSPIRMapTableEntry.name: worpQoSPIRMapTableEntry
worpQoSPIRMapTableEntry.description: This table represents the entry for the worpQoSPIRMapTable.

worpQoSPIRMapTableIndex.name: worpQoSPIRMapTableIndex
worpQoSPIRMapTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the table.

worpQoSPIRMapRuleName.name: worpQoSPIRMapRuleName
worpQoSPIRMapRuleName.description: This parameter specifies the PIR Rule name corresponds to this index.

worpQoSPIRMapSrcMacIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapSrcMacIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapSrcMacIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Source MAC Address Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRMapDstMacIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapDstMacIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapDstMacIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Destination MAC Address Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRMapSrcIpAddrIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapSrcIpAddrIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapSrcIpAddrIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Source IP Address Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRMapDstIpAddrIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapDstIpAddrIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapDstIpAddrIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Destination IP Address Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRMapSrcPortIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapSrcPortIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapSrcPortIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Source TCP/UDP Port Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRMapDstPortIndexList.name: worpQoSPIRMapDstPortIndexList
worpQoSPIRMapDstPortIndexList.description: This parameter specifies the Destination TCP/UDP Port Classification for the PIR Rule. This is a display string consists of index number of the PIR MAC Table entries with comma seperated. Value 0 indicates that this list is disabled.

worpQoSPIRTable.name: worpQoSPIRTable
worpQoSPIRTable.description: This Table holds the Packet Identification Rule(PIR) information for QoS feature.

worpQoSPIRTableEntry.name: worpQoSPIRTableEntry
worpQoSPIRTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the worpQoSPIRTable.

worpQoSPIRTableIndex.name: worpQoSPIRTableIndex
worpQoSPIRTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the table.

worpQoSPIRRuleName.name: worpQoSPIRRuleName
worpQoSPIRRuleName.description: This parameter specifies the Packet Identification Rule(PIR) Name.

worpQoSPIRRuleBitMask.name: worpQoSPIRRuleBitMask
worpQoSPIRRuleBitMask.description: This parameter specifies which Packet classification rules are enabled. It is a Bit Mask field. Bits are defined as follows Bit0 - Dst MAC rule Enabled. Bit1 - Src MAC rule Enabled. Bit2 - Prity rule Enabled. Bit3 - Vlan ID rule Enabled. Bit4 - Ether value rule Enabled. Bit5 - ToS rule Enabled. Bit6 - IP PROTOCOL rule Enabled. Bit7 - Dst IP Addr rule Enabled. Bit8 - Src IP Addr rule Enabled. Bit9 - Dst Port rule Enabled. Bit10 - Src Port rule Enabled. Bit11 - PPPoE Encapsulation rule Enabled.

worpQoSPIRIPToSLow.name: worpQoSPIRIPToSLow
worpQoSPIRIPToSLow.description: This Parameter specifies the lower limit for the ToS (Types Of Service) classification.

worpQoSPIRIPToSHigh.name: worpQoSPIRIPToSHigh
worpQoSPIRIPToSHigh.description: This Parameter specifies the higher limit for the ToS classification.

worpQoSPIRIPToSMask.name: worpQoSPIRIPToSMask
worpQoSPIRIPToSMask.description: This Parameter specifies The ToS Mask which will be used to perform bitwise and operation with incoming Packet's ToS values and it will be checked again Lower & Hight limit the ToS Low, ToS High configuraiton.

worpQoSPIRIPProtocolIds.name: worpQoSPIRIPProtocolIds
worpQoSPIRIPProtocolIds.description: This Parameter specifies the Protocol Classification for the incoming packet.

worpQoSPIREtherPriorityLow.name: worpQoSPIREtherPriorityLow
worpQoSPIREtherPriorityLow.description: This parameter specifies the lower limit for the 802.1p classificaiton for the incoming packet.

worpQoSPIREtherPriorityHigh.name: worpQoSPIREtherPriorityHigh
worpQoSPIREtherPriorityHigh.description: This parameter specifies the Higher limit for the 802.1p classificaiton for the incoming packet.

worpQoSPIRVlanId.name: worpQoSPIRVlanId
worpQoSPIRVlanId.description: This parameter specifies the VLAN classification for the incoming packet.

worpQoSPIREtherType.name: worpQoSPIREtherType
worpQoSPIREtherType.description: This parameter specifies the Ether type classification for the incoming ethernet frame.

worpQoSPIREtherValue.name: worpQoSPIREtherValue
worpQoSPIREtherValue.description: This parameter specifies the Ether Value classificaiton for the incoming ethernet frame.

worpQoSPIRPPPoEEncapsulation.name: worpQoSPIRPPPoEEncapsulation
worpQoSPIRPPPoEEncapsulation.description: This parameter specifies the PPPoE (Point-to-point Protocol Over Ethernet) Encapsulation status for the incoming ethernet frame.

worpQoSPIRPPPoEProtocolId.name: worpQoSPIRPPPoEProtocolId
worpQoSPIRPPPoEProtocolId.description: This parameter specifies the protocol id inside the PPPoE Encapsulation data for the incoming ethernet frame.

worpQoSPIRMapTableIndexVal.name: worpQoSPIRMapTableIndexVal
worpQoSPIRMapTableIndexVal.description: This parameter specifies the index of the worpQoSPIRMapTable.

worpQoSPIRTableEntryStatus.name: worpQoSPIRTableEntryStatus
worpQoSPIRTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the worpQoSPIRTable status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

worpQoSSFClassTable.name: worpQoSSFClassTable
worpQoSSFClassTable.description: This Table holds the Service Flow Classification (SFC) information for QoS feature.

worpQoSSFClassTableEntry.name: worpQoSSFClassTableEntry
worpQoSSFClassTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the worpQoSSFClassTable.

worpQoSSFClassTableIndex.name: worpQoSSFClassTableIndex
worpQoSSFClassTableIndex.description: This parameter specifies the index number of the entry in the worpQoSSFClassTable.

worpQoSSFClassName.name: worpQoSSFClassName
worpQoSSFClassName.description: This parameter specifies the Service Flow Class Name.

worpQoSSFClassSchedularType.name: worpQoSSFClassSchedularType
worpQoSSFClassSchedularType.description: This parameter specifies the type of Scheduler to be used for this Service Flow. Select 1 for rtps - Real Time Polling Service 2 for be - Best Effort.

worpQoSSFClassDirection.name: worpQoSSFClassDirection
worpQoSSFClassDirection.description: This parameter specifies the Direction of the Service Flow.

worpQoSSFClassStatus.name: worpQoSSFClassStatus
worpQoSSFClassStatus.description: This parameter specifies the Status of the Service Flow.

worpQoSSFClassMIR.name: worpQoSSFClassMIR
worpQoSSFClassMIR.description: This parameter specifies the Maximum Information Rate(MIR) for this Service Flow. This value is represented in Kbps.

worpQoSSFClassCIR.name: worpQoSSFClassCIR
worpQoSSFClassCIR.description: This parameter specifies the Comitted Information Rate(CIR) for this Service Flow. This value is represented in Kbps.

worpQoSSFClassMaxLatency.name: worpQoSSFClassMaxLatency
worpQoSSFClassMaxLatency.description: This parameter specifies the Latency for this Service Flow. This is represented in milliseconds.

worpQoSSFClassTolerableJitter.name: worpQoSSFClassTolerableJitter
worpQoSSFClassTolerableJitter.description: This parameter specifies the Jitter for this Service Flow. This is represented in milliseconds.

netIpWirelessCfgSubnetMask.name: netIpWirelessCfgSubnetMask

netCfgStaticRouteStatus.name: netCfgStaticRouteStatus

ethernetInActivityTimer.name: ethernetInActivityTimer
ethernetInActivityTimer.description: This parameter is used to monitor the ethernet interface for every specified number of minutes. The value 0 disables monitoring.

netCfgPrimaryDNSIpAddress.name: netCfgPrimaryDNSIpAddress
netCfgPrimaryDNSIpAddress.description: This parameter is to configure the Primary DNS IP Address to be used by this product.

netCfgSecondaryDNSIpAddress.name: netCfgSecondaryDNSIpAddress
netCfgSecondaryDNSIpAddress.description: This parameter is to configure the Secondary DNS IP Address to be used by this product.

wirelessInActivityTimerInSecs.name: wirelessInActivityTimerInSecs
wirelessInActivityTimerInSecs.description: This parameter is used to monitor the wireless interface for every specified number of seconds. The value 0 disables monitoring. It can be configured from 5 to 600 seconds.

ripConfigTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for ripConfigTable.

ripInterfaceName.name: ripInterfaceName
ripInterfaceName.description: This parameter shows the available interfaces for which the rip can be configured.

ripInterfaceStatus.name: ripInterfaceStatus
ripInterfaceStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable the rip for the particular interface.

ripInterfaceAuthType.name: ripInterfaceAuthType
ripInterfaceAuthType.description: This parameter represents the authentication type used for rip configuration.

ripInterfaceAuthKey.name: ripInterfaceAuthKey
ripInterfaceAuthKey.description: This parameter is used to configure the authentication key for the authentication type.

ripInterfaceVersionNum.name: ripInterfaceVersionNum
ripInterfaceVersionNum.description: This parameters allows to configure the rip version verion.

ripReceiveOnly.name: ripReceiveOnly
ripReceiveOnly.description: This parameter allows to configure the interface to receive only RIP version 1 and/or RIP verison 2 packets.

vlanStatus.name: vlanStatus
vlanStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the VLAN functionality. Select 1 to enable the VLAN functionality and 2 to disable the VLAN functionality.

mgmtVLANIdentifier.name: mgmtVLANIdentifier
mgmtVLANIdentifier.description: This parameter represents the management VLAN Identifier (ID).

mgmtVLANPriority.name: mgmtVLANPriority
mgmtVLANPriority.description: This parameter represents the management VLAN priority, giving eight (2^3) priority levels with the highest priority as seven.

vlanEthCfgTable.name: vlanEthCfgTable
vlanEthCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure the VLAN parameters for the ethernet interface.

vlanEthCfgTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the Vlan Configuration table.

vlanEthCfgTableIndex.name: vlanEthCfgTableIndex
vlanEthCfgTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the physical interface and used as index to this table.

vlanMode.name: vlanMode
vlanMode.description: This parameter is used to set the VLAN Mode for the physical interface.

accessVLANId.name: accessVLANId
accessVLANId.description: This parameter is used to set the access VlanId for the physical interface.

accessVLANPriority.name: accessVLANPriority
accessVLANPriority.description: This parameter is used to set the access Vlan priority, which varies from 0 to 7 with 7 having highest priority.

untaggedFrames.name: untaggedFrames
untaggedFrames.description: This parameter is used to set the option to allow the untagged frames.

vlanEthTrunkTable.description: This table is used to configure the VLAN trunk parameters for ethernet interface.

vlanEthTrunkTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the Vlan Trunk Configuration table.

vlanEthTrunkTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the vlan trunk table index and also represents the ethernet interface.

vlanEthTrunkTableSecIndex.name: vlanEthTrunkTableSecIndex
vlanEthTrunkTableSecIndex.description: This parameter represents the trunk table secondary index.

ethVLANTrunkId.name: ethVLANTrunkId
ethVLANTrunkId.description: This parameter is used to set the trunk id.

vlanEthTrunkTableEntryStatus.name: vlanEthTrunkTableEntryStatus
vlanEthTrunkTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the vlan trunk table status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

filteringCtrl.name: filteringCtrl
filteringCtrl.description: This parameter stores the information whether the Global Filterng is Enabled or Disabled. If this parameter is set to enabled, then the filtering is enabled. If this parameter is disabled, then filtering will be disabled. Select 1 to enable this parameter and 2 to disable this parameter.

intraBSSFiltering.name: intraBSSFiltering
intraBSSFiltering.description: This parameter controls the wireless to wireless communication. If this parameter is set to enabled, then wireless to wireless communication is not allowed. If this parameter is set disabled, then wireless to wireless communication is allowed. Select 1 to enable the wireless to wireless communication and 2 to disable wireless to wireless communication.

etherProtocolFilteringCtrl.name: etherProtocolFilteringCtrl
etherProtocolFilteringCtrl.description: This parameter is used to configure the interface. By default, the parameter is set to disabled. The filter can be enabled either for Ethernet, Wireless or All Interface. Select 1 for ethernet, 2 for wireless, 3 for all interfaces and 4 for disable.

etherProtocolFilteringType.name: etherProtocolFilteringType
etherProtocolFilteringType.description: If the specific protocol is not available in the ethernet protocol table, then this parameter specifies the action that needs to be taken on the packet. If this parameter is set to passthru (1), then specific protocol will be allowed. If this parameter is set to block (2), then specific protocol will be denied.

etherProtocolFilterTable.name: etherProtocolFilterTable
etherProtocolFilterTable.description: This table contains the two byte hexadecimal values of the protocols. The packets whose protocol field matches with any of the entries in this table will be forwarded or dropped.

etherProtocolFilterTableEntry.name: etherProtocolFilterTableEntry
etherProtocolFilterTableEntry.description: This parameter represents an entry in the protocol filter table. This table supports upto 64 entries.

etherProtocolFilterTableIndex.name: etherProtocolFilterTableIndex
etherProtocolFilterTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index of the ethernet protocol Filtering table.

etherProtocolFilterProtocolName.name: etherProtocolFilterProtocolName
etherProtocolFilterProtocolName.description: This parameter represents a two byte hexadecimal value for the Ethernet protocol to be filtered.

etherProtocolFilterProtocolNumber.name: etherProtocolFilterProtocolNumber
etherProtocolFilterProtocolNumber.description: This parameter represents the value in the protocol field of the Ethernet packet. The value is of 4-digit Hex format. Example: The value of IP protocol is 0800. The value of ARP protocol is 0806.

etherprotocolFilterStatus.name: etherprotocolFilterStatus
etherprotocolFilterStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the ethernet protocol filtering. Select 1 to block, 2 to passthru.

etherProtocolFilterTableStatus.name: etherProtocolFilterTableStatus
etherProtocolFilterTableStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the ethernet protocol filtering table status. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

staticMACAddrFilterTable.name: staticMACAddrFilterTable
staticMACAddrFilterTable.description: This table provides the MAC address of the stations on the wired and the wireless interface; the MAC addresses will be given in pairs. Stations listed in the Static MAC Address filter will have no traffic forwarded by the device. This way Multicast traffic exchanged between stations or servers can be prevented, from being transmitted over the wireless medium when both stations are actually located on the wired backbone.

staticMACAddrFilterTableEntry.name: staticMACAddrFilterTableEntry
staticMACAddrFilterTableEntry.description: This parameter identifies the entry in the Static MAC address filter table. This table support upto 200 entries.

staticMACAddrFilterTableIndex.name: staticMACAddrFilterTableIndex
staticMACAddrFilterTableIndex.description: This parameter is user defined that represents the index of the Static MAC Filtering table.

staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACAddress.name: staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACAddress
staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACAddress.description: This parameter represents the MAC address of the station on the wired interface of the device.

staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACMask.name: staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACMask
staticMACAddrFilterWiredMACMask.description: This parameter represents the MAC address of the filter wired MASK.

staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACAddress.name: staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACAddress
staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACAddress.description: This parameter represents the MAC address for the wireless interface.

staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACMask.name: staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACMask
staticMACAddrFilterWirelessMACMask.description: This parameter represents the mask for the wireless interface MAC address.

staticMACAddrFilterComment.name: staticMACAddrFilterComment
staticMACAddrFilterComment.description: This parameter is used for an optional comment associated to the staticMACAddrFilter entry.

staticMACAddrFilterTableEntryStatus.name: staticMACAddrFilterTableEntryStatus
staticMACAddrFilterTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the status of the staticMACAddrFilterTable. Select It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

advancedFilterTable.name: advancedFilterTable
advancedFilterTable.description: This table is used to configure the advanced filtering using protocol name and direction.

advancedFilterTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for advancedFilterTable. This table supports up to 5 entries.

advancedFilterTableIndex.name: advancedFilterTableIndex
advancedFilterTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index of the advanced filtering table.

advancedFilterProtocolName.name: advancedFilterProtocolName
advancedFilterProtocolName.description: This parameter represents the protocol name to be filtered. (DenyIPX RIP, Deny IPX SAP, Deny IPX LSP, Deny IP Broadcasts, Deny IP Multicasts)

advancedFilterDirection.name: advancedFilterDirection
advancedFilterDirection.description: This parameter represents the direction of the individual entry in the advanced filter table. The direction can be enabled either for Ethernet to Wireless, Wireless to Ethernet or both. Select 1 for ethernet2wireless, 2 for wireless2ethernet, 3 for both.

advancedFilterTableEntryStatus.name: advancedFilterTableEntryStatus
advancedFilterTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the row status of the advanced filtering table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

tcpudpPortFilterCtrl.name: tcpudpPortFilterCtrl
tcpudpPortFilterCtrl.description: This parameter is used to configure the Tcp Udp Port Filtering. Select 1 to enable and 2 to disable the Tcp Udp Port Filtering.

tcpudpPortFilterTable.description: This table contains the configurations for the Tcp Udp Port Filtering table.

tcpudpPortFilterTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for tcpudpPortFilterTable. This table supports up to 64 entries.

tcpudpPortFilterTableIndex.name: tcpudpPortFilterTableIndex
tcpudpPortFilterTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as index for the TcpUdp port filter table.

tcpudpPortFilterProtocolName.name: tcpudpPortFilterProtocolName
tcpudpPortFilterProtocolName.description: This parameter represents the protocol name for the tcpudpPortFilter.

tcpudpPortFilterPortNumber.name: tcpudpPortFilterPortNumber
tcpudpPortFilterPortNumber.description: This parameter represents the Port number for the tcpudpPortFilter.

tcpudpPortFilterPortType.description: This parameter represents the port type for this TcpUdp Port filter table. The parameter can be either TCP or UDP or TCP/UDP. Select 1 for TCP, 2 for UDP and 3 for both.

tcpudpPortFilterInterface.name: tcpudpPortFilterInterface
tcpudpPortFilterInterface.description: This parameter is used to configure the interface. By default, the parameter is set to All Interfaces. The filter can be enabled either for Ethernet, Wireless or All Interface. Select 1 for only Ethernet, 2 for only Wireless and 3 for allInterfaces.

tcpudpPortFilterTableEntryStatus.name: tcpudpPortFilterTableEntryStatus
tcpudpPortFilterTableEntryStatus.description: The parameter indicates the status of the TCP/UDP portfilter table entry. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6)
