stormFilterInterface.description: This parameter is used to configure the interface.The filter can be enabled either for Ethernet or Wireless. 1 for Ethernet 2 for Wireless

stormMulticastThreshold.name: stormMulticastThreshold
stormMulticastThreshold.description: This parameter is used to provide the threshold value of the multicast packets to be processed for the interface. If threshold value for multicast packets is set to '0', no filtering will take place (filtering will be disabled).Excess packets will be dropped if packets are more than threshold value.To disable MultiCast packets filtering for this interface this variable should be set to '0'(zero).

stormBroadcastThreshold.name: stormBroadcastThreshold
stormBroadcastThreshold.description: This parameter is used to provide the threshold value of the broadcast packets to be processed for interface.If threshold value for broadcast packets is set to '0', no filtering will take place (filtering will be disabled). Excess packets will be dropped if packets are more than threshold value.To disable Broadcast wireless packets filtering,this variable should be set to '0' (Zero).

dhcpServerStatus.name: dhcpServerStatus
dhcpServerStatus.description: This parameter indicates if the DHCP server/relay is enabled or disabled in the device.

dhcpMaxLeaseTime.name: dhcpMaxLeaseTime
dhcpMaxLeaseTime.description: This parameter represents the maximum lease time in 100th seconds for the IP address assigned by the DHCP server to the DHCP client.

dhcpServerIfTable.name: dhcpServerIfTable
dhcpServerIfTable.description: This table is used to configure the DHCP server for a particular interface.

dhcpServerIfTableEntry.name: dhcpServerIfTableEntry
dhcpServerIfTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the dhcpServerIfTable.

dhcpServerIfTableIndex.name: dhcpServerIfTableIndex
dhcpServerIfTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the dhcpServerIfTable.

dhcpServerInterfaceType.name: dhcpServerInterfaceType
dhcpServerInterfaceType.description: This parameter shows the list of interfaces for which the DHCP can be configured.

dhcpServerNetMask.name: dhcpServerNetMask
dhcpServerNetMask.description: This parameter is used to configure the mask for the interface shown.

dhcpServerDefaultGateway.name: dhcpServerDefaultGateway
dhcpServerDefaultGateway.description: This parameter represents the IP Address of the gateway or router that the DHCP Server will assign to the DHCP client.

dhcpServerPrimaryDNS.name: dhcpServerPrimaryDNS
dhcpServerPrimaryDNS.description: This parameter represents the primary DNS Server IP Address to be assinged to a DHCP Client.

dhcpServerSecondaryDNS.name: dhcpServerSecondaryDNS
dhcpServerSecondaryDNS.description: This parameter represents the secondary DNS Server IP Address to be assinged to a DHCP Client.

dhcpServerDefaultLeaseTime.name: dhcpServerDefaultLeaseTime
dhcpServerDefaultLeaseTime.description: This parameter represents the default lease time, in 100th seconds, for the IP address assigned by the DHCP server to the DHCP client.

dhcpServerIfTableComment.name: dhcpServerIfTableComment
dhcpServerIfTableComment.description: This parameter represents an optional comment for this table entry.

dhcpServerIfTableEntryStatus.name: dhcpServerIfTableEntryStatus
dhcpServerIfTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the row status for the dhcpServerIfTable. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

dhcpServerIpPoolTable.name: dhcpServerIpPoolTable
dhcpServerIpPoolTable.description: This table contains the pools of IP Addresses that the DHCP server will assign to the DHCP clients.

dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntry.name: dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntry
dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntry.description: This parameter represents entries in the dhcpServerIpPoolTable.

dhcpServerIpPoolTableIndex.name: dhcpServerIpPoolTableIndex
dhcpServerIpPoolTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as the index for the IP Address Pool table.

dhcpServerIpPoolInterface.name: dhcpServerIpPoolInterface
dhcpServerIpPoolInterface.description: This parameter shows the list of interfaces for which the DHCP server can be configured.

dhcpServerIpPoolStartIpAddress.name: dhcpServerIpPoolStartIpAddress
dhcpServerIpPoolStartIpAddress.description: This parameter represents the start IP address for this DHCP IP Address IP Pool Table entry.

dhcpServerIpPoolEndIpAddress.name: dhcpServerIpPoolEndIpAddress
dhcpServerIpPoolEndIpAddress.description: This parameter represents the end IP address for this DHCP IP Address IP Pool Table entry.

dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntryStatus.name: dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntryStatus
dhcpServerIpPoolTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the row status for the dhcpServerIpPoolTable. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

dhcpRelayServerTable.name: dhcpRelayServerTable
dhcpRelayServerTable.description: This table contains a list of DHCP servers to which the DHCP Agent will communicate with.

dhcpRelayServerTableEntry.name: dhcpRelayServerTableEntry
dhcpRelayServerTableEntry.description: This parameter represents and entry in the DHCP Server table.

dhcpRelayServerTableIndex.name: dhcpRelayServerTableIndex
dhcpRelayServerTableIndex.description: This parameter is used as the index to this dhcpRelayServerTable.

dhcpRelayServerIpAddress.name: dhcpRelayServerIpAddress
dhcpRelayServerIpAddress.description: This parameter represents the IP address of the DHCP server that shall receive DHCP requests from the device.

dhcpRelayServerTableEntryStatus.name: dhcpRelayServerTableEntryStatus
dhcpRelayServerTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the row status for the dhcpRelayServerTable. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

sysTypeTable.name: sysTypeTable
sysTypeTable.description: This table holds the information about the supported and current modes of the device.

sysTypeTableEntry.name: sysTypeTableEntry
sysTypeTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry status for the sysTypeTable. It can hold one entry.

sysTypeRadioIfIndex.name: sysTypeRadioIfIndex
sysTypeRadioIfIndex.description: This parameter represents the physical interface (radio) and index for the sysType Table.

sysTypeMode.name: sysTypeMode
sysTypeMode.description: This parameter is used to configure the mode of the radio(s). Please refer the sysTypeSupportedMode object for the supported modes. The modes are represented in numbers as follows: AP (1), CLIENT (2), WDS (3), BSU (4), *Applies in TMP(tsunamiMP) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* EndPointA (4), *Applies in QB(tsunamiQuickBridge) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* SU (5) *Applies in TMP(tsunamiMP) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* EndPointB (5) *Applies in QB(tsunamiQuickBridge) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily*

sysTypeActiveMode.name: sysTypeActiveMode
sysTypeActiveMode.description: This parameter shows the active mode of the radio(s). The configured mode will take effect after the reboot. The modes are represented in numbers as follows: AP (1), CLIENT (2), WDS (3), BSU (4), *Applies in TMP(tsunamiMP) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* EndPointA (4), *Applies in QB(tsunamiQuickBridge) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* SU (5) *Applies in TMP(tsunamiMP) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily* EndPointB (5) *Applies in QB(tsunamiQuickBridge) mode - please refer sysFeatureProductFamily*

sysTypeSupportedMode.name: sysTypeSupportedMode
sysTypeSupportedMode.description: This parameter displays the supported modes of operations complying with the license.

sysTypeSupportedFreqDomains.name: sysTypeSupportedFreqDomains
sysTypeSupportedFreqDomains.description: This parameter displays the supported frequency domains.

sysTypeFreqDomain.name: sysTypeFreqDomain
sysTypeFreqDomain.description: This parameter is used to configure the frequency domain. The following list shows in detail: - United States All: 5.3 + 5.4 with DFS and 5.8 without DFS - United States Adhoc: 5.8 without DFS only - United States 2.4 GHz - World All - World 4.9 GHz (4.940 – 4.990 GHz) - World 2.4 GHz (2.400 – 2.472 GHz) - World 2.3 GHz - World 2.5 GHz - Canada 5 GHz (5.250 – 5.350 & 5.470 – 5.600 & 5.650 – 5.725 GHz all bands with DFS) - Europe 5.8 GHz (5.725 – 5.850 GHz with DFS) - Europe 5.4 GHz (5.470 – 5.600 & 5.650 – 5.725 GHz both with DFS) - Europe 2.4 GHz (2.400 – 2.4825 GHz) - Russia 5 GHz (5.150 – 6.080 GHz without DFS) - Taiwan 5 GHz (5.500 – 5.700 with DFS & 5.725 – 5.825 GHz without DFS) - United State 5 GHz (5.250 – 5.350 & 5.470 – 5.725 GHz with DFS & 5.725 – 5.850 GHz without DFS) - Canada 5.8 GHz. - Russia Frequency Convertor. - Japan 2.4 GHz (2412 - 2472 MHz) - Japan 4.9 GHz (4920 - 4980 MHz and 5040 - 5080 MHz). - UK 5.8 GHz (5725 - 5795 MHz and 5825 - 5850 MHz) - World 5.9GHz - United States 5.3 and 5.8 GHz - India 5.8GHz.

sysTypeActiveFreqDomain.name: sysTypeActiveFreqDomain
sysTypeActiveFreqDomain.description: This parameter shows the active frequency domain. The following list shows in detail: - United States All: 5.3 + 5.4 with DFS and 5.8 without DFS - United States Adhoc: 5.8 without DFS only - United States 2.4 GHz - World All - World 4.9 GHz (4.940 – 4.990 GHz) - World 2.4 GHz (2.400 – 2.472 GHz) - World 2.3 GHz - World 2.5 GHz - Canada 5 GHz (5.250 – 5.350 & 5.470 – 5.600 & 5.650 – 5.725 GHz all bands with DFS) - Europe 5.8 GHz (5.725 – 5.850 GHz with DFS) - Europe 5.4 GHz (5.470 – 5.600 & 5.650 – 5.725 GHz both with DFS) - Europe 2.4 GHz (2.400 – 2.4825 GHz) - Russia 5 GHz (5.150 – 6.080 GHz without DFS) - Taiwan 5 GHz (5.500 – 5.700 with DFS & 5.725 – 5.825 GHz without DFS) - United State 5 GHz (5.250 – 5.350 & 5.470 – 5.725 GHz with DFS & 5.725 – 5.850 GHz without DFS) - Canada 5.8 GHz. - Russia Frequency Convertor - Japan 2.4 GHz (2412 - 2472 MHz) - Japan 4.9 GHz (4920 - 4980 MHz and 5040 - 5080 MHz). - UK 5.8 GHz (5725 - 5795 MHz and 5825 - 5850 MHz) - World 5.9GHz - United States 5.3 and 5.8 GHz - India 5.8GHz.

sysNetworkMode.name: sysNetworkMode
sysNetworkMode.description: This parameter is used to configure the network mode of the device.

sysActiveNetworkMode.name: sysActiveNetworkMode
sysActiveNetworkMode.description: This parameter is shows the network mode of the device. This can be configured in the sysNetworkMode.

sysConfCountryCode.description: This attribute identifies the country in which the station is operating to set the frequency band. The first two octets of this string is the two character country code as described in document ISO/IEC 3166-1. This object is not supported for the current products, please refer sysTypeFreqDomain for configuring the Frequency band. Below is the list of mapping of country codes to country names. igmpSnoopingGlobalStatus.name: igmpSnoopingGlobalStatus
igmpSnoopingGlobalStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable the IGMP snooping. Only passive snooping is supported. This feature is supported only in bridge mode.

igmpMembershipAgingTimer.name: igmpMembershipAgingTimer
igmpMembershipAgingTimer.description: This parameter represents the time after which the IGMP multicast group age-outs/elapses.

igmpRouterPortAgingTimer.name: igmpRouterPortAgingTimer
igmpRouterPortAgingTimer.description: This parameter represents the time after which the IGMP router port age-outs/elapses.

igmpForcedFlood.name: igmpForcedFlood
igmpForcedFlood.description: If this paramter is set with Yes, all unregistered multicast traffic and membership reports will be flooded to all ports.

sysCountryCode.name: sysCountryCode
sysCountryCode.description: This attribute identifies the country in which the station is operating. The first two octets of this string is the two character country code as described in document ISO/IEC 3166-1. Below is the list of mapping of country codes to country names. This object is deprecated and please use sysConfCountryCode to set the country code. AL - ALBANIA DZ - ALGERIA AR - ARGENTINA AM - ARMENIA AU - AUSTRALIA AT - AUSTRIA AZ - AZERBAIJAN BH - BAHRAIN BY - BELARUS BE - BELGIUM BZ - BELIZE BO - BOLIVIA BR - BRAZIL BN - BRUNEI DARUSSALAM BG - BULGARIA CA - CANADA CL - CHILE CN - CHINA CO - COLOMBIA CR - COSTA RICA HR - CROATIA CY - CYPRUS CZ - CZECH REPUBLIC DK - DENMARK DO - DOMINICAN REPUBLIC EC - ECUADOR EG - EGYPT EE - ESTONIA EU - EUROPEAN UNION FI - FINLAND FR - FRANCE GE - GEORGIA DE - GERMANY GR - GREECE GT - GUATEMALA HK - HONG KONG HU - HUNGARY IS - ICELAND IN - INDIA ID - INDONESIA IR - IRAN IE - IRELAND I1 - IRELAND - 5.8GHz IL - ISRAEL IT - ITALY JP - JAPAN J2 - JAPAN2 JM - JAMAICA JO - JORDAN KZ - KAZAKHSTAN KP - NORTH KOREA KR - KOREA REPUBLIC K2 - KOREA REPUBLIC2 KW - KUWAIT LV - LATVIA LB - LEBANON LI - LIECHTENSTEIN LT - LITHUANIA LU - LUXEMBOURG MO - MACAU MK - MACEDONIA MT - MALTA MY - MALAYSIA MX - MEXICO MC - MONACO MA - MOROCCO NL - NETHERLANDS NZ - NEW ZEALAND NO - NORWAY OM - OMAN PK - PAKISTAN PA - PANAMA PE - PERU PH - PHILIPPINES PL - POLAND PT - PORTUGAL PR - PUERTO RICO QA - QATAR RO - ROMANIA RU - RUSSIA SA - SAUDI ARABIA CS - SERBIA & MONTENEGRO SG - SINGAPORE SK - SLOVAK REPUBLIC SI - SLOVENIA ZA - SOUTH AFRICA ES - SPAIN SE - SWEDEN CH - SWITZERLAND SY - SYRIA TW - TAIWAN TH - THAILAND TR - TURKEY UA - UKRAINE AE - UNITED ARAB EMIRATES GB - UNITED KINGDOM G1 - UNITED KINGDOM - 5.8GHz US - UNITED STATES UW - UNITED STATES - World U1 - UNITED STATES - DFS UY - URUGUAY VE - VENEZUELA VN - VIETNAM

sysInvMgmtComponentTable.name: sysInvMgmtComponentTable
sysInvMgmtComponentTable.description: This table holds the system's inventory management component features.

sysInvMgmtComponentTableEntry.name: sysInvMgmtComponentTableEntry
sysInvMgmtComponentTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the sysInvmgmtComponentTable

sysInvMgmtCompTableIndex.name: sysInvMgmtCompTableIndex
sysInvMgmtCompTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for sysInvMgmtCompTable.

sysInvMgmtCompSerialNumber.name: sysInvMgmtCompSerialNumber
sysInvMgmtCompSerialNumber.description: This parameter identifies the system component serial number

sysInvMgmtCompName.name: sysInvMgmtCompName
sysInvMgmtCompName.description: This parameter identifies the system component name.

sysInvMgmtCompId.name: sysInvMgmtCompId
sysInvMgmtCompId.description: This parameter shows the identifier for the component.

sysInvMgmtCompVariant.name: sysInvMgmtCompVariant
sysInvMgmtCompVariant.description: This parameter identifies the system component variant number.

sysInvMgmtCompReleaseVersion.name: sysInvMgmtCompReleaseVersion
sysInvMgmtCompReleaseVersion.description: This parameter identifies the system component release version number.

sysInvMgmtCompMajorVersion.name: sysInvMgmtCompMajorVersion
sysInvMgmtCompMajorVersion.description: This parameter identifies the system component major version number.

sysInvMgmtCompMinorVersion.name: sysInvMgmtCompMinorVersion
sysInvMgmtCompMinorVersion.description: This parameters identifies the system component minor version number.

sysInvMgmtSecurityID.name: sysInvMgmtSecurityID
sysInvMgmtSecurityID.description: This parameter represents the system's Security ID.

sysInvMgmtDaughterCardAvailability.name: sysInvMgmtDaughterCardAvailability
sysInvMgmtDaughterCardAvailability.description: This parameter shows the availability of the daughter card.

sysFeatureCtrlID.name: sysFeatureCtrlID
sysFeatureCtrlID.description: This parameter is used to represent the control ID for the system feature.

sysFeatureNumRadios.name: sysFeatureNumRadios
sysFeatureNumRadios.description: This parameter shows the number of radios supported. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureFreqBand.name: sysFeatureFreqBand
sysFeatureFreqBand.description: This parameter shows the supported frequency bands. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureOutBandwidth.name: sysFeatureOutBandwidth
sysFeatureOutBandwidth.description: This parameter represents the outward bandwidth in multiples of 1Mbps. This is based on the license file

sysFeatureInBandwidth.name: sysFeatureInBandwidth
sysFeatureInBandwidth.description: This parameter represents the inward bandwidth in multiples of 1Mbps. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureOpMode.name: sysFeatureOpMode
sysFeatureOpMode.description: This parameter represents the current operational mode of the device. This is based on the license file.

sysLicFeatureTable.name: sysLicFeatureTable
sysLicFeatureTable.description: This table contains a list of features that the current image supports and indicates if this feature is licensed or not. Each row represents a supported feature. Supported indicates if the current image supports the image while licensed indicates that a license is available to use this feature. Based on the license information in this table, some MIB groups/subgroups/tables are enabled or disabled.

sysLicFeatureTableEntry.name: sysLicFeatureTableEntry
sysLicFeatureTableEntry.description: This table parameter represents the entry for the sysLicFeatureTable. This table can hold a maximum of 50 entries.

sysLicFeatureTableIndex.name: sysLicFeatureTableIndex
sysLicFeatureTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the sysLicFeatureTable.

sysLicFeatureType.name: sysLicFeatureType
sysLicFeatureType.description: This parameter represents the feature type and shows the code of the feature.

sysLicFeatureValue.name: sysLicFeatureValue
sysLicFeatureValue.description: This parameter represents feature value i.e., enabled or disabled.

sysFeatureCumulativeBandwidth.name: sysFeatureCumulativeBandwidth
sysFeatureCumulativeBandwidth.description: This parameter represents the cumulative bandwidth of the device. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureNumEtherIf.name: sysFeatureNumEtherIf
sysFeatureNumEtherIf.description: This parameter represents the number of ethernet interfaces supported. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureBitmap.name: sysFeatureBitmap
sysFeatureBitmap.description: This parameter represents the bit map for the features enabled/disabled. The value for this parameter is interpreted as a bitfield and the respective modules are shown below: BRIDGE-MODE-ONLY = 0, WORP = 1, Intra Cell Blocking = 2, Intra BSS Blocking = 3, VLAN = 4, STATIC-ROUTING = 5, NAT = 6, FILTERING = 7. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureNumOfSatellitesAllowed.name: sysFeatureNumOfSatellitesAllowed
sysFeatureNumOfSatellitesAllowed.description: This parameter represents the max number of satellites supported. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureProductFamily.name: sysFeatureProductFamily
sysFeatureProductFamily.description: This parameter represents the product family. This is based on the license file.

sysFeatureProductClass.name: sysFeatureProductClass
sysFeatureProductClass.description: This parameter represents the product class. This is based on the license file.

sysLicRadioInfoTable.name: sysLicRadioInfoTable
sysLicRadioInfoTable.description: This table holds the license file parameters for the radio(s).

sysLicRadioInfoTableEntry.name: sysLicRadioInfoTableEntry
sysLicRadioInfoTableEntry.description: This table parameter represents the entry for the sysLicRadioInfoTable.

sysLicRadioInfoTableIndex.name: sysLicRadioInfoTableIndex
sysLicRadioInfoTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the sysLicRadioInfoTable.

sysLicRadioCompID.name: sysLicRadioCompID
sysLicRadioCompID.description: This parameter represents the component ID for the radio(s).

sysLicRadiovariantID.name: sysLicRadiovariantID
sysLicRadiovariantID.description: This parameter represents the variant ID for the radio(s).

sysLicRadioAntennaType.name: sysLicRadioAntennaType
sysLicRadioAntennaType.description: This parameter represents the Antenna type supported for the radio(s).

sysLicRadioAntennaMimoType.name: sysLicRadioAntennaMimoType
sysLicRadioAntennaMimoType.description: This parameter represents the Antenna MIMO type for the radio(s).

sysMgmtCfgChangeCnt.name: sysMgmtCfgChangeCnt
sysMgmtCfgChangeCnt.description: This parameter represents the number of successful commits that has taken place since the system was rebooted last.

sysMgmtCfgCommit.name: sysMgmtCfgCommit
sysMgmtCfgCommit.description: This parameter is used to apply the changed configurations to the device. Always this should be SET with value '1'. The values available on GET or the read values are defined as follows: 200 : Commit Successful 201 : Commit Successful and reboot the device. Please check the object sysMgmtCfgErrorMsg for Commit status and other information on errors. P.S: Usual commit operation needs atleast 3 seconds and changes in wireless parameters needs upto 60 seconds time interval before sending the response.

sysMgmtCfgRestore.name: sysMgmtCfgRestore
sysMgmtCfgRestore.description: This parameter is used to restore the device to last working configuration

sysMgmtCfgErrorMsg.name: sysMgmtCfgErrorMsg
sysMgmtCfgErrorMsg.description: This parameter displays the latest error message occured in configuration.

sysMgmtReboot.name: sysMgmtReboot
sysMgmtReboot.description: This parameter is used to reboot device. Select 1 to reboot.

sysMgmtFactoryReset.name: sysMgmtFactoryReset
sysMgmtFactoryReset.description: This parameter is used to reset the device to factory settings.

sysMgmtLoadTextConfig.name: sysMgmtLoadTextConfig
sysMgmtLoadTextConfig.description: This parameter is used to load the configurations from the Text Based Configuration File.

sysContactEmail.name: sysContactEmail
sysContactEmail.description: This parameter is used to identify the email address of the contact person for a device. The length of the email address should be between 6 to 32

sysContactPhoneNumber.name: sysContactPhoneNumber
sysContactPhoneNumber.description: This parameter is used to identify the phone number of the contact person for a device.

sysLocationName.name: sysLocationName
sysLocationName.description: This parameter is used to store the location of the system.

sysGPSLongitude.name: sysGPSLongitude
sysGPSLongitude.description: This parameter is used to represent Longitude.

sysGPSLatitude.name: sysGPSLatitude
sysGPSLatitude.description: This parameter is used to represent Latitude.

sysGPSAltitude.name: sysGPSAltitude
sysGPSAltitude.description: This parameter is used to display the elevation of an access point from a known level.

productDescr.name: productDescr
productDescr.description: A textual description of the entity. This value should includes the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.

systemName.name: systemName
systemName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.

mgmtSnmpReadPassword.name: mgmtSnmpReadPassword
mgmtSnmpReadPassword.description: This parameter is used for the SNMP password and represents the read-only community name used in the SNMP protocol.It is used for reading objects from the SNMP agent. The password should be treated as write-only and would be returned as asterisks. User is not allowed to set since it is same as mgmtSnmpReadWritePassword

mgmtSnmpReadWritePassword.name: mgmtSnmpReadWritePassword
mgmtSnmpReadWritePassword.description: This parameter is used to represent the read-write community name used in the SNMP protocol. This parameter is used for reading and writing objects to the SNMP agent. This parameter should be treated as write-only and returned as asterisks.

mgmtSnmpAccessTable.name: mgmtSnmpAccessTable
mgmtSnmpAccessTable.description: This table holds the objects of the mgmtSnmpAccessTable.

mgmtSnmpAccessTableEntry.name: mgmtSnmpAccessTableEntry
mgmtSnmpAccessTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the mgmtSnmpAccessTable.

mgmtSnmpAccessTableIndex.name: mgmtSnmpAccessTableIndex
mgmtSnmpAccessTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for the mgmtSnmpAccessTable and this is not-accessible.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTable.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTable
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTable.description: This table contains the destination IP address and community password for the trap delivery.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntry.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntry
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry for the mgmtSnmpTrapHostTable.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIndex.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIndex
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIndex.description: This parameter represents the index for SNMP Trap Host table. This table supports upto 5 rows.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIPAddress.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIPAddress
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableIPAddress.description: This parameter is used to represent the IP address of the management station that will receive SNMP traps from the device.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTablePassword.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTablePassword
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTablePassword.description: This parameter is used to represent the password that is sent with the SNMP trap messages to allow the host to accept or reject the traps. The trap host will accept SNMP traps if the sent password matches the host's password. This parameter returns asterisks on get. This is not allowed to set because it is same as mgmtSnmpReadWritePassword.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableComment.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableComment
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableComment.description: This parameter represents the comment for the row in the SNMP Trap Host Table.

mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntryStatus.name: mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntryStatus
mgmtSnmpTrapHostTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configure the row status for the SNMP Trap Host table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

mgmtSnmpVersion.name: mgmtSnmpVersion
mgmtSnmpVersion.description: This parameter is used to configure the SNMP Version. The version v2c provides the security by means of community passwords and the version v3 provides highest security with authentication and encryption.

mgmtSnmpV3SecurityLevel.name: mgmtSnmpV3SecurityLevel
mgmtSnmpV3SecurityLevel.description: This parameter allows to select the security level for SNMPV3. The level noAuthNoPriv is not supported.

mgmtSnmpV3AuthProtocol.name: mgmtSnmpV3AuthProtocol
mgmtSnmpV3AuthProtocol.description: This parameter allows to configure the authentication protocol in SNMPV3. Select 2 for MD5 and 3 for SHA.

mgmtSnmpV3AuthPassword.name: mgmtSnmpV3AuthPassword
mgmtSnmpV3AuthPassword.description: This parameter allows to configure the authentication password for the authentication protocol.

mgmtSnmpV3PrivProtocol.name: mgmtSnmpV3PrivProtocol
mgmtSnmpV3PrivProtocol.description: This parameter allows to configure the privacy (encryption) protocol in SNMPV3. Select 2 for DES and 3 for AES-128.

mgmtSnmpV3PrivPassword.name: mgmtSnmpV3PrivPassword
mgmtSnmpV3PrivPassword.description: This parameter allows to configure the privacy (encryption) password for the privacy protocol.

httpPassword.name: httpPassword
httpPassword.description: This parameter represents the system access password for the HTTP interface to manage the device via a web browser.This parameter would return the value in asterisks.

httpPort.name: httpPort

tftpOpType.description: This parameter represents the type of TFTP operation that is to be executed. The upload functionality will transfer the specified file from the device to the TFTP server. tftpOpStatus.description: This parameter represents the TFTP operation status. 1 - Idle, 2 - Download in progress 3 - Download Success 4 - Download Failure 5 - Signature check in progress 6 - Signature check failed 7 - Write on flash is in progress 8 - Write on flash is failed 9 - Upload in progress 10 - Upload success 11 - Upload failed

globalTrapStatus.name: globalTrapStatus

mgmtAccessTable.name: mgmtAccessTable

syslogHostTableEntryStatus.description: This parameter is used to configue the status of the Syslog host entry table. A maximum of 5 entries can be added to this table. It can be configured as active(enable) -1, notInService(disable) - 2, createAndGo(create row) -4, destroy(delete) - 6

eventLogPriority.description: This parameter is used to configure the priority for the event log table. Select 1 for Emergency, 2 for alert, 3 for critical, 4 for error, 5 for warning, 6 for notice, 7 for info and 8 for debug.

eventLogReset.name: eventLogReset
eventLogReset.description: This parameter is used to reset/clear the event log table. When this parameter is set, then all enteries in the event log table are deleted/cleared. Select (1) to reset the table.
